Problem Statement:
You are given an array of n positive integers a[1..n] and an integer k. Your task is to find the maximum length of a subarray (i.e., a contiguous segment) such that the sum of its elements is less than or equal to k.Input:
The first line contains two integers n and k (1 ≤ n ≤ 10^5, 1 ≤ k ≤ 10^9).
The second line contains n integers a₁, a₂, ..., aₙ (1 ≤ a[i] ≤ 10^4).

Output:
Print a single integer — the maximum length of a subarray whose sum is ≤ k.
